SIMULATION REPORT
Synchronous RAM Design using Verilog HDL
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Objective

To design and simulate a simple synchronous RAM capable of performing read and write operations using Verilog HDL.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Software Used

Xilinx Vivado
Verilog HDL

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Operations Implemented

Write Operation
Read Operation
Address-Based Memory Access
Synchronous Data Storage
Synchronous Data Retrieval

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Input Values Used

Address = 001
Input Data = AA (10101010)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Simulation Procedure

The synchronous RAM module was designed using Verilog HDL.
A separate testbench was created to apply read and write operations.
Behavioral simulation was run in Xilinx Vivado.
Waveforms were observed to verify correct memory storage and retrieval operations.

=========================================================================================================================================================
Waveform Analysis

The waveform shows the operation of the synchronous RAM during write and read processes.
Initially, the output dout is undefined (XX) because no valid data has been read from memory yet.

During the first clock cycle:

we = 1
Operation performed = Write Operation

Address selected:
_________________

addr = 001

Input data:
____________

din = 10101010 (AA)

The data is written into the selected memory location.

After the write operation is completed:

we = 0
Operation performed = Read Operation

The RAM reads the stored data from the same address location and sends it to the output.

Therefore, the output becomes:

dout = AA

The waveform correctly verifies both RAM write and read operations.

